column5: Anybody have any water temps for Red Lake, ON? I would even settle for water temps on Lac Seul. T-minus 1 week for my crew! Thanks!
I took the boat for a spin on wabigoon lake today and the water was 13 degrees celcius. I would imagine red lake and lac seul would be a few degrees colder since they're deeper and further north.
Interesting, I was on a local lake this morning (lat 44.8) and the temp was just a hair above 14. The 'eyes were biting.
fished cedar lake yesterday and cliff the day before.main lake water around 48 f and some bays 54 f.little south of red lake but shouldbe close to the same i would think.
I saw a lot of mid 50's water temps yesterday on LOTW's. Highest I saw was 61 in a mud fishing for pike.
